http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Visakhapatnam/Centre-to-consider-one-time-grant-for-gaming-centre/article13993809.ece

Union Minister for Commerce Nirmala Sitharaman has promised MP and State BJP president K. Haribabu to consider sanctioning Rs.100 crore as one-time grant under export facilitation fund for setting up an IT, animation, and gaming centre in the city.In reply to a letter submitted by Dr. Haribabu, Ms. Sitharaman said the request would be examined to take necessary action.Job prospectsMeanwhile, vice-chairman of Vizag Development Forum Naresh Kumar hoped that the project would be sanctioned for Visakhapatnam shortly to create lot of employment opportunities to the local youth.